cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with object detection and mapping using visual and inertial sensors, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) categories. The use of deep networks for detection and nonlinear filtering for memory suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) component. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing (cs.CL) for labeling objects, although this is not the main focus of the paper. Overall, cs.CV and cs.RO are the most likely categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
